&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SingleStore is seeking a Forward Deployed Engineer (FDE) to operate at the intersection of solution architecture, technical delivery, and customer partnership. This role combines elements of a solutions architect, technical account manager, and solution engineer, with a strong emphasis on execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an FDE, you will serve as a trusted technical advisor and sounding board for customers, helping them design, implement, and scale real-time data solutions using SingleStore. You will work closely with customers to understand their business objectives, translate them into technical strategies, and drive those solutions into production. This role requires a delivery mindset, strong technical depth, and the ability to lead both strategic conversations and hands-on execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role and Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner directly with customers to understand their architecture, use cases, and business goals, and translate them into scalable technical solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement end-to-end solutions integrating SingleStore into existing application and data ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead whiteboard sessions to shape ideas, define architecture, and convert concepts into technical specifications and execution plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a proactive thought partner, bringing ideas and guiding conversations rather than reacting to requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own delivery of high-impact initiatives from concept through production, ensuring successful outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide hands-on support, including troubleshooting, optimization, and applying pragmatic solutions or fixes when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Sales, Solutions Engineering, Product, and Engineering teams to align customer needs with product capabilities and roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help customers prioritize and operationalize their data initiatives, balancing ambition with practical delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Feed insights from customer engagements back into Product and Engineering to influence roadmap and improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in solution architecture, solution engineering, or technical consulting (pre-sales and/or post-sales).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong foundation in databases, distributed systems, or software engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience delivering production-grade solutions in customer-facing environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience integrating complex systems across data pipelines, applications, and infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate ambiguous requirements into clear technical plans and drive execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with enterprise customers, particularly in financial services or high-tech environments, is highly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and organizational skills, with the ability to guide both technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to balance technical innovation with pragmatic delivery and realistic scoping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alignment with product capabilities and roadmap, ensuring solutions are both impactful and feasible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
